Brazilian Stock Movers: AmBev, Eletropaulo, MRV and Telesp

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-08-11T20:31:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/brazilian-stock-movers-ambev-eletropaulo-mrv-and-telesp.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index climbed 3.8 percent to 53,343.11.  Cia. de Bebidas das Americas (AMBV4 BS) gained 4.9 percent
to 48.34 reais.  Latin America ’s largest brewer, known as AmBev,
said second-quarter normalized profit rose 20.4 percent to 1.84
billion reais ($1.13 billion), according to a statement today.  Eletropaulo Metropolitana SA (ELPL4 BS) lost 5.4 percent to
29.61 reais. The Brazilian unit of AES Corp. posted a second-
quarter profit of 255.4 million reais, a 47 percent drop from a
year earlier.  MRV Engenharia & Participacoes SA (MRVE3 BS) gained 5.8
percent to 11.67 reais.  Brazil ’s fifth-biggest homebuilder by
revenue said it will buy back 10 million of its common shares
during the next year.  Telecomunicacoes de Sao Paulo SA (TLPP3)  (TLPP4 BS) rose 1.1
percent to 45.20 reais. Telefonica SA’s Brazil unit, known as
Telesp, said it plans to buy back as many as 2.7 million
preferred shares by Oct. 20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  